<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1771" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1771">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.74/37.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Price</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 29, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your despatch No. 69. Subject of agreement with Panama concerning the
                            establishment of radio telegraph stations in territory of that Republic
                            has been considered by the Joint Army and Navy Board. The report of that
                            board was approved by the President November 17, 1913.</p>
                        <p>The first paragraph of this report provides for giving to United States
                            Government the monopoly of all means of radio communication <pb facs="1158" n="1042" xml:id="pg_1042"/> within the Panaman territory
                            and cancelling of all concessions for stations not at this time in
                            actual operation, if such exist.</p>
                        <p>You are instructed to inform the Government of Panama in this sense in an
                            informal manner.</p>
                        <p>Further instructions will be sent in near future.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>